<plot>Filmed at the Orlando, Florida baseball school/camp ran by Joe Stripp. The narrative written by sports-writer Stanley Frank and spoken by Dan Seymour takes a look at veteran baseball players, including Joe Tinker (of Tinker-to-Evans-to-Chance fame), as they instruct the camp students on the best ways to play the various baseball positions, plus pitching, catching and hitting lessons.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?111214</url></doc>
